07-19 11:05:27.035 debug OkHttp 991, \"Europe in the Middle Ages\" p. 258) \"In the arithmetical theorems in Euclid's Elements VII-IX, numbers had been represented by line segments to which letters had been attached, and the geometric proofs in al-Khwarizmi's Algebramade use of lettered diagrams; but all coefficients in the equations used in the Algebra are specific numbers, whether represented by numerals or written out in words. href=\"/wiki/%D8%AC%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AF\" title=\"جليد\">جليد</a> والحالة الغازيّة على شكل <a href=\"/wiki/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B1_%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%A1\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"بخار ماء\">بخار href=\"/wiki/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A1\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"الهواء\">الهواء</a> على هيئة <a href=\"/wiki/%D8%B3%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%A8\" title=\"سحاب\">سحاب</a> (غيوم)، وأحياناً أخرى
